   <body>
      <context>
         <note>Battery cables and signal cables must be routed separately
to reduce noise.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the plate in the bottom left side of the power section
of the UPS cabinet.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the cable channel cover in the power section of
the UPS cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Power Section of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_75-100kwups_removecoversforsignal_w120mm_0000165933.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the signal cables through the top or bottom of the
I/O section of the UPS cabinet to the control terminal block TB1. </p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the I/O Section of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_pxc_nam_75-100_kva_terminal_control_block_tb1_in_io_section_120mm_0000111798.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Only in systems with adjacent battery cabinet(s): Route the signal cables from the adjacent battery cabinet(s) through
the cable channel in the power section of the UPS cabinet to the control
terminal block TB1 in the I/O section of the UPS cabinet as shown.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/100kva_hole_side-panel_for-Bcabinet_Iview_120mm_0000116652.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the signal cables through the top or bottom of the
I/O section of the UPS cabinet through the cable channel in the power
section of the UPS cabinet to the external connection board 0P2553. </p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_75-100_kva_with_transformer_external_connection_board_0p2553_120mm_0000161952.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
